      },
      "date": "2018-10-08 15:48:02.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1: Code-Review+1\n\n> Sebastien, can you please confirm these sptlrpc messages at startup\n > are not important to keep?\n\nIt is fine to quiet those messages. I guess they were meant to look like the ones for supported checksum algorithms. They just say which GSS modules are loaded: krb5, ssk, etc.",
